          <h2>üéØ Our Mission</h2>
          <p>We aim to build social and economic consequences for caste-based hate and discrimination ‚Äî without waiting for slow-moving institutions or government bodies to act.</p>
          <p>We must build a better society for future generations.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="highlight-box">
          <h2>‚ùì Why This Exists</h2>
          <p>Casteism is not just a private belief. It directly affects hiring, safety, and dignity.</p>
          <p>When casteist threats are made publicly ‚Äî especially on media or online ‚Äî there must be public accountability.</p>
          <p>Employers, professional networks, and communities must take responsibility by refusing to empower caste bigots.</p>
          <p>It is a criminal offense and should be treated as such.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="highlight-box">
          <h2>üí• What We Can Do</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Document verifiable casteist statements, threats, or actions.</li>
            <li>Record the name, employer, caste, location, and proof for each person.</li>
            <li>Pressure institutions (companies, parties, media, etc.) to take action ‚Äî and to exclude those who take pride in caste in any form.</li>
            <li>Track whether the person has been warned, fired, defended, or ignored.</li>
            <li>Create long-term social stigma around casteist behavior.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="policy-box">
          <h2>üîÑ Removal Policy</h2>
          <p>We believe people can change ‚Äî but only with time, accountability, and public responsibility.</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Ages 16‚Äì20:</strong> Entries are removed after 2 years if there are no repeat offenses.</li>
            <li><strong>Ages 21+:</strong> Entries are removed after 10 years of a clean record and a public apology.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Early removal requests must include proof of transformation, such as:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>A sincere public apology</li>
            <li>Ongoing anti-caste work</li>
            <li>Surrender or cooperation with legal action</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="highlight-box">
          <h2>üèõ Why Without the Government?</h2>
          <p>Government action is often slow, and in many cases, politically compromised or run by those with casteist bias.</p>
          <p>We don't need to wait. Industry bodies, communities, and employers can take action now.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Blacklist casteists from white-collar employment</li>
            <li>Deny public-facing roles to those with a history of caste hate</li>
            <li>Build pressure through transparency and undeniable proof</li>
          </ul>
